<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The fact that it makes your VT raids less loot efficent is none of our business and will never be. Splitted Vt can keep our early(cough) or late crew busy so it is all good for us. I understand your concerns, with the mass of characters you has to equip, you need a maximum of loot income in minimum time to keep all happy. It is your choice to have a 300 characters rooster, it makes alot of things easier but has downsides too.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, we have 158 non gimps/retired/etc. tagged in our guild. About 30-40 consist of our core, on all the friggin time. With another 40 being semi-consistent raiders. Another 60 being mild raiders. We have a points system so advanced it makes my head hurt, but it provides an even distrubution, those hard cores... some already have 2+ aten loots, and a lot have 5-6 VT loots.<br>
<br>
Now let's look at this:<br>
PATCH DAY: Early patch, servers up. ToS primetime.<br>
ToS does the bare minimum in 6-7 hours with their 35 (which according to Kordin is the RIGHT &quot;non-zerg&quot; amount), killing AHR unless of course they wipe to TvK with that incapable force. This nets them 24 loots I believe (I might be off 1 or 2).<br>
<br>
Day after patch. ToS logs in and one of two things happens. <br>
<br>
One, TWC decides to go kill the two blobs and the tower that was left up. Netting us 9 loots, 6 of which would have been ToS's the night before with an adequate force, the other 3 would have been available as I doubt we'd bother going in for just one of the towers. ToS now has to look for another spot, Ssra is surely cleared by now, perhaps some uber Behemoth loot? or BoT towers?<br>
<br>
Two, TWC doesn't bother with VT the night before. Tos returns and spends 3-4 hours with their inadequate force to get 9 loots. So now ToS has spent two solid raid days getting 33 loots.<br>
<br>
OK now, Patch Day... long patch. Pops on TWC primetime. We clear everything in 4-5 hours. Afterwords, we get a 24 man force and go finish off anything that might be left up like Cursed or Emperor occasionally. Netting us 30 loots from VT, and most nights 3-6 more.<br>
<br>
Day two, we have the day to work on our PoP progression. Reflagging a couple people. Or working on RZ, granted OOP hasn't cockblocked (must have 600 people flagged all those kills that became neccesary again once TWC started attempting).<br>
<br>
So which is more effecient 36 loots in one day for 70 people? Or 33 loots in two days for 35 people?<br>
<br>
Same loot, double the people. But we get a whole day to work on progression so we can leave you in VT to fuck up warders for ToN.<br>
